user.biography:
👩‍🎓 Biophysicist @ UCL 🧬
🏃‍♀️ IronMan & Sprinter
🎥 Translating science on YouTube
My programmes, approved by GB Olympic expert ⬇️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Natacha Oceane in London, United Kingdom. May be an image of 1 person, standing and sunglasses.

node.text:
Something tells me date night after a 5 hour workout is gonna be one to remember 🍝🥟🍱 And by something I mean my stomach speaking to me in 7 different languages for the last hour 👀
⠀⠀
Also, very important: the workout was for a YouTube video, I would never ☠️😅

More than a year of rehab work is finally coming to an end 🥺 I’m still not where I was but I’m finally not scared of pushing my body any more and feel so freeee again 😆🤍 Falling down a few stairs really got me good for a little while, but I’m just the happiest to feel like myself and to start making YouTube videos again next week! 💃💃 I feel like a new person and I feel grateful for every minute I get to do what I love. So damn excited to see all your beautiful faces soon! 🥳

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Natacha Oceane on August 02, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and outdoors.

node.text: Hello beautiful people ♥️ I’ve missed you and I’m sorry for being so quiet 🙊 I’ve been in my own little world working away on something very important to me these last few months, and I haven’t had much time to myself. To be honest, life’s been unsustainable and imbalanced and giving me flashbacks to my IronMan days when only one thing in the world existed. COVID hit us pretty hard for a while, and we spent a few weeks not able to eat much and feeling like we were on a never-ending boat trip 🛳 but we had each other and are just thankful to be back to ourselves. My back has been holding up real well so I’ve been finding my old strength and feeling like myself again too, so life’s good and I feel extra lucky 🥺 All the heartwarming messages and emails these last few weeks were the sweetest things of all time and I’m sorry there isn’t enough time in the day to reply to each and every one of them! I’m so excited to be back soon with a head full of ideas of videos and experiments and science I want to share 👩‍🔬 Thank you for the insane kindness always and for staying the best support anywhere! 🤍

node.text: Health and fitness is a long, looong game ☺️ I can never say enough that there’s no race, there’s so much time to transform yourself. Good things take time and the best things take even longer. Quick fixes are BS (I wish they weren’t too, but they just are) so focus on the sum of lots of little things you do for yourself spread out over months and years, not days and weeks. All the days I spent in bed last year with my spinal injury thinking I’d never move or feel like my same self again, I underestimated how much change can happen in time myself too. And now here we are, thinking about a diving holiday next year 🤿🥺 However far away it feels, just remember that the tortoise won the race 🐢😘

node.text:
Leg + 🍑 demolition day is here! 👷‍♀️ This one needs zero equipment and is gonna hit your legs in places you didn’t know existed even if you’re used to training at the gym and with resistance at the moment 😉💃 ⠀
⠀⠀
Even though I have my weights back 🏋️‍♀️🥰 I never neglect bodyweight movements cause we wanna move good instead of just looking like we move good 🙏 ⠀
⠀⠀
Don’t forget to save 💾 for when you’re readyyy! ⠀
⠀⠀
🤸‍♂️ Open leg lunge to squat jump (3 x 16 total): as you hit the lunge, really focus on your bodyweight going through the heel of your front foot so the back foot’s really just for balance ⠀
⠀⠀
🤸‍♂️ Prisoner in’n’outs (3 x 30s): stay up on your toes and don’t feel bad if it takes a second to get the rhythm! You’ll keep it once you got it ☺️ ⠀
⠀⠀
🤸‍♂️ Double squat calf raises (3 x 14): raising up all the way onto your toes in the lower AND top position of the squat ✌️ Two times 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️ ⠀
⠀⠀
🤸‍♂️ BW hip thrust calf raise (3 x 12): squeezing our glutes to lift our hips all the way through and holding for the shortest little pause at the top 😝 ⠀
⠀⠀
🤸‍♂️ Kneel to alt knee drive (3 x 16 total) ⠀
⠀⠀
🤸‍♂️ Bear to down dog knee taps (3 x 14 total) ⠀
⠀⠀
I go for 30-60s rest times between sets and complete all sets of a move before moving to the next, but you can always turn it into a circuit and do your thing 😘 ⠀
⠀⠀
Keep moving however makes you happyyy and keep smiling 💛

node.text:
Today’s session had me sweating and pulling faces enough to cover a lifetime of workouts 💦🥵 I’m currently under instructions from my physio to focus on overhead, unilateral and asymmetric weighted exercises to rebuild my core strength and get it stabilising real well like it used to. Kinda sounds exactly like how I love to train anyway, so no need to tell me twice 👀💃 Feeling fortunate as heck today that my back is allowing me to return to what I love 🥺 ⠀
⠀⠀
Today I went for: ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡ Overhead DB cleans: 2 x 12 per side ⠀
⠀⠀

node.text:
Hot little HIIT kinda day! 💦😝 A whole load of sweat + endorphins are all yours for just 15 minutes of your day, and you don’t need any equipment! 😘 ⠀
⠀⠀
We’ve got 5 moves: I like to go for 30s of exercise followed by 30s of rest before switching to the next move for 3 rounds, so it’s a circuit (I’ll explain why I love this format with a HIIT Science Explained soooon! 👩‍🔬) That’s technically just 14.5 mins so you get 30s leftover to tell yourself how freaking badass you are 🤸‍♂️ ⠀
⠀⠀
Double tap ♥️ and hit SAVE 💾 so you always have it close! ⠀
⠀⠀
💦 Squat to scissor step: staying light on our toes through the scissor step. These should sound quiet if you’re getting them right 🤫😘 ⠀
⠀⠀
💦 Bear squat kickbacks: press down into the ground through your shoulders and remember to keep your upper body and core engaged! ⠀
⠀⠀
💦 Rocket launches: reach all the way upppp onto your toes ⠀
⠀⠀
💦 Triple position mountain climbers: try to keep your hip position fixed and drive your knee up fast into each of the positions ⠀
⠀⠀
💦 Crab elbow to toe taps: simplify these and just go for knee to elbow taps if you prefer ♥️ ⠀
⠀⠀
After 3 rounds, you’ve got 30s all to yourself to go find your crown you HIIT queen or king 👑 and we’re at 15 minutes! 💃 ⠀
⠀⠀
P.s. don’t forget to switch up the rest times or the number of rounds to make it feel perfect for you. Each and every workout is about feeling good and finishing with a smile, and you know your body better than anyone else! 💛 ⠀
⠀⠀
Song is Huncho Jack 🔥🎶

node.text:
A year ago a back injury totally stopped me from moving how I love. I’m nowhere near as strong or fast or powerful or coordinated as I was but wowow movement has NEVER made me happier and damn that’s worth so much more. Now I get to relearn and regain all those parts of my fitness and really appreciate how lucky I am the whole way ☺️ Movement is the greatest gift and I’m in love with the feeeeeling 🤸‍♀️🤸‍♀️ ⠀
⠀⠀
P.S. no need to feel bad about any downstairs neighbours, our apartment’s on an overhang over a garden so nobody hears my bouncy workouts ☺️♥️♥️

node.text: Just a small appreciation for my best friend. For never letting me lose faith in myself and for always believing in me, even on the days when I couldn’t move from my bed and felt myself losing hope. My doctor told me when I was little that the people you surround yourself with will shape who you are, and I feel so lucky to be surrounded by you. Foreverever ♥️

node.text:
It allll starts with core! 🔥😍 ⠀
⠀⠀
It makes the biggest difference to think about hitting your core as a whole and bring in more than just the top layer of ab muscle if you’re tryna get real strong and keep your body working as one 💪 ⠀
⠀⠀
Hit SAVE and double tap and you’ll have it forever ♥️ ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡Kneeling rotational chop (3 x 30s): it’s super, super important that you stay squeezing your abs throughout and rotate through the obliques so your hips stay facing forwards 🙌 These work even better with a cable machine in the gym! ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡Pike walk-ins (3 x 6): keep your legs as straight as possible with your core engaged, and shift your bodyweight through to your shoulders ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡Shoulder tap plank jacks (3 x 30s): keep your elbows soft (not locked out) and really try to keep your hips down with your core squeezed throughout ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡Heel tap sit backs (3 x 12 total): engage the core and focus on staying level (no rotating!) and stable as you move onto one arm 🙏 ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡Low to high wood chops (3 x 10 per side): range of motion is super important here! We want to rotate to bring your hands past your hips in both phases of the chop and that’ll really wake up your core 😴 ⠀
⠀⠀
⚡Russian twists bicycle kicks (3 x 30s): find a rhythm and goooo 🚲 ⠀
⠀⠀
The trick to these is to really engage your core in each move and focus on which body parts are supposed to be moving and which are supposed to be holding still 🙏 ⠀
⠀⠀
Hope you’re staying safe + healthy + happy! 💛
